    "chemicalDescription": [
      "rh-Polypeptide-60 is a single chain recombinant human peptide, produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is directly isolated from a human cell which codes for Superoxide Dismutase 1 used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 154 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
